September 6, 2017 - Back to School Meetup at Eanes ISD

Hey y’all! Our next meetup is on September 6th, 2017, at Eanes ISD! Assistant IT Director Chris Miller will be sharing his insights on how Eanes ISD scaled their MDM for the school year. Emily will also revisit tools that every Apple Admin should have in their toolbox (pencilcase? trapper keeper?). Food and drinks will be provided by Jamf (thanks!).

Agenda

  • 6:00pm - Arrive, Mingle, Pizza
  • 6:30pm - Welcomes and introductions with our host Eanes ISD
  • 6:35pm - Chris Miller, “The Art of Scaling Eanes MDM: A Million Ways to Dork Things Up”
  • 7:20pm - Dr. Emily Kausalik, Apple Admin Tools for Fun and Profit
  • 7:30pm - Q&A, open discussion

Registration

Registration is now available on Jamf Nation.

If you’d like to RSVP but do not have a Jamf Nation account, please consider creating one (it’s free!). If you’d rather not, you can RSVP by sending an email to hello@austinappleadmins.org.

If you’d like to speak at a future meetup in Austin please let us know.
